WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:00:17.658 --> 00:00:18.741
Coffee?

3
00:00:18.783 --> 00:00:20.033
For sure.

4
00:00:20.075 --> 00:00:21.325
Thanks. man.

5
00:00:22.283 --> 00:00:23.658
You ready for next week?

6
00:00:23.700 --> 00:00:24.783
What's next week?

7
00:00:24.825 --> 00:00:26.658
Superhuman evasion training.

8
00:00:26.700 --> 00:00:28.366
We have to get recertified.

9
00:00:28.408 --> 00:00:30.075
Look. I...
I get the need.

10
00:00:30.116 --> 00:00:31.491
but it's the worst.

11
00:00:31.533 --> 00:00:32.658
When I was on the force.

12
00:00:32.700 --> 00:00:34.259
you had to do hand-to-hand
training all the time.

13
00:00:34.283 --> 00:00:35.467
The guy comes at you
with a knife.

14
00:00:35.491 --> 00:00:36.616
you gotta be ready.

15
00:00:36.658 --> 00:00:39.366
but. uh. this is...
th-this is something else.

16
00:00:39.408 --> 00:00:41.283
I'm supposed to learn
to tuck and roll

17
00:00:41.325 --> 00:00:42.491
away from a guy

18
00:00:42.533 --> 00:00:43.991
who can shoot lasers
from his eyes.

19
00:00:44.033 --> 00:00:46.158
or control minds.

20
00:00:46.200 --> 00:00:49.450
or kick a goddamn schoolbus
to the moon?

21
00:00:49.491 --> 00:00:51.491
It's the job.

22
00:00:51.533 --> 00:00:53.491
You're awful calm
about it.

23
00:00:53.533 --> 00:00:55.116
Hell. last time
you sprained your back.

24
00:00:55.158 --> 00:00:56.033
You...

25
00:00:56.075 --> 00:00:57.075
Aw. shit. wait.

26
00:00:57.116 --> 00:00:58.634
you're not even
gonna be here. are you?

27
00:00:58.658 --> 00:01:00.283
Sucks to be you!

28
00:01:01.283 --> 00:01:02.825
I'll be living it up
in London.

29
00:01:02.866 --> 00:01:04.616
seeing the sights.
eating Indian food.

30
00:01:04.658 --> 00:01:05.866
Enjoy getting laser burn.

31
00:01:05.908 --> 00:01:07.908
Oh. you're gonna be gone
the whole time?

32
00:01:07.950 --> 00:01:08.950
All friggin' week?

33
00:01:08.991 --> 00:01:09.783
Two.

34
00:01:09.825 --> 00:01:11.533
All of Matt's spring break.

35
00:01:11.575 --> 00:01:13.241
The boy is obsessed
with The Beatles.

36
00:01:13.283 --> 00:01:14.575
He wants to go
to Abbey Road.

37
00:01:14.616 --> 00:01:16.783
he wants to visit
Apple Records.

38
00:01:16.825 --> 00:01:18.592
I might even get to see
some things I want to see.

39
00:01:18.616 --> 00:01:19.450
if we have time.

40
00:01:19.491 --> 00:01:21.450
And it's just the two of you?

41
00:01:21.491 --> 00:01:22.950
You sure about that. Steve?

42
00:01:22.991 --> 00:01:24.325
I thought you two
hated each other

43
00:01:24.366 --> 00:01:25.991
with the burning fury
of a thousand suns.

44
00:01:27.408 --> 00:01:29.158
Well. maybe a hundred.

45
00:01:29.200 --> 00:01:33.033
I mean. Matt.
he had it rough. you know.

46
00:01:33.075 --> 00:01:35.450
but he's really
pulled himself together.

47
00:01:35.491 --> 00:01:37.950
With what you told me
that kid was doing?

48
00:01:37.991 --> 00:01:40.450
The stealing. the drugs?

49
00:01:40.491 --> 00:01:42.325
How'd you turn that around?

50
00:01:43.283 --> 00:01:44.700
Good morning.

51
00:01:44.741 --> 00:01:45.950
It wasn't easy.

52
00:01:45.991 --> 00:01:46.991
The thing is.

53
00:01:47.033 --> 00:01:48.176
when Molly and I
first got together.

54
00:01:48.200 --> 00:01:49.325
he was living with his dad.

55
00:01:49.366 --> 00:01:51.783
and he was just running wild.

56
00:01:51.825 --> 00:01:54.450
Kid was a real asshole.

57
00:01:54.491 --> 00:01:56.200
You saw the shiner he gave me.

58
00:01:56.241 --> 00:01:58.033
That's all behind us now.

59
00:01:58.075 --> 00:02:00.408
He stared down his demons.
and he...

60
00:02:00.450 --> 00:02:03.325
damn it. he conquered them.

61
00:02:03.366 --> 00:02:06.075
I've never done anything
that hard in my life.

62
00:02:06.116 --> 00:02:08.450
We're so damn proud
of the guy...

63
00:02:08.491 --> 00:02:10.616
of the man that he's becoming.

64
00:02:10.658 --> 00:02:12.533
So he wants to go to London.

65
00:02:12.575 --> 00:02:14.866
Molly and I scraped together
enough to make it happen.

66
00:02:14.908 --> 00:02:15.950
We wanted to show him

67
00:02:15.991 --> 00:02:18.783
how much we appreciate
all his hard work.

68
00:02:20.866 --> 00:02:22.783
I never had a kid of my own.

69
00:02:22.825 --> 00:02:23.884
I wasn't there
when he was born.

70
00:02:23.908 --> 00:02:25.950
I didn't teach him
how to ride a bike.

71
00:02:25.991 --> 00:02:26.991
or throw a ball...

72
00:02:29.325 --> 00:02:30.200
...but in a few months.

73
00:02:30.241 --> 00:02:31.991
when he walks
across that stage.

74
00:02:32.033 --> 00:02:33.450
and accepts that diploma...

75
00:02:34.991 --> 00:02:37.075
...that is my son.

76
00:02:38.491 --> 00:02:41.783
Oh. you... you just take
all the time you need.

77
00:02:41.825 --> 00:02:43.616
Why don't I just
make some hot cocoa

78
00:02:43.658 --> 00:02:45.283
to cheer up my sweet boy?

79
00:02:45.325 --> 00:02:47.325
Come on. like you're not
crying on my shoulder

80
00:02:47.366 --> 00:02:49.075
every time you don't get
a second date?

81
00:02:50.325 --> 00:02:51.366
What was...

82
00:03:21.741 --> 00:03:24.450
We were supposed
to be inside.

83
00:03:24.491 --> 00:03:25.825
I should never have trusted

84
00:03:25.866 --> 00:03:28.491
the flawed calculations
of a clone.

85
00:03:28.533 --> 00:03:29.491
Clone?

86
00:03:29.533 --> 00:03:30.908
I am not!

87
00:03:33.408 --> 00:03:35.950
This was always
the plan.

88
00:03:35.991 --> 00:03:37.533
The president
is targeting us.

89
00:03:37.575 --> 00:03:39.450
so we shatter the illusion
of his safety.

90
00:03:39.491 --> 00:03:41.241
It's not enough
for us to kill him.

91
00:03:41.283 --> 00:03:42.658
It has to be a spectacle.

92
00:03:44.783 --> 00:03:47.200
You'd know this
if you were truly the original.

93
00:03:48.200 --> 00:03:49.825
Oh. god. oh. god. oh. god...

94
00:03:49.866 --> 00:03:51.116
Refreshing.

95
00:03:51.158 --> 00:03:52.158
Kind of tickles.

96
00:03:52.200 --> 00:03:54.033
Mm. I prefer
a higher caliber.

97
00:03:59.158 --> 00:04:00.658
Huh?

98
00:04:00.700 --> 00:04:03.075
I order...

99
00:04:03.116 --> 00:04:04.741
I order...

100
00:04:04.783 --> 00:04:07.241
I order you...

101
00:04:07.283 --> 00:04:08.741
You order what?

102
00:04:14.075 --> 00:04:15.450
Kill that one
and move on!

103
00:04:15.491 --> 00:04:17.366
Your eye is as replaceable
as you are.

104
00:04:17.408 --> 00:04:19.366
I am the original!

105
00:04:20.575 --> 00:04:21.866
Steve. look out!

106
00:04:35.200 --> 00:04:36.491
Sorry I'm late!

107
00:04:36.533 --> 00:04:38.325
Red Rush.
get this guy out of here!

108
00:04:38.366 --> 00:04:39.575
Focus on evac!

109
00:04:39.616 --> 00:04:42.741
We can deal with these two
once the area is clear!

110
00:04:46.366 --> 00:04:48.241
We can take it from here!

111
00:04:48.283 --> 00:04:50.825
Fall back. help us
evacuate civilians!

112
00:04:50.866 --> 00:04:51.825
Yes. ma'am!

113
00:04:51.866 --> 00:04:53.033
Damn it! Run!

114
00:04:54.991 --> 00:04:56.866
War Woman...

115
00:04:58.033 --> 00:05:01.241
Please. you couldn't just
sit this one out?

116
00:05:01.283 --> 00:05:03.075
Let us kill the President?

117
00:05:03.116 --> 00:05:04.408
Haven't you earned a day off?

118
00:05:04.450 --> 00:05:05.450
Not our style.

119
00:05:05.491 --> 00:05:06.491
Sorry.

120
00:05:07.491 --> 00:05:08.783
This isn't
a spectator sport!

121
00:05:08.825 --> 00:05:09.825
Move!

122
00:05:13.116 --> 00:05:14.116
No!

123
00:05:15.908 --> 00:05:18.228
Stay together. stay together.
stay together. stay together!

124
00:05:22.866 --> 00:05:24.033
Don't move.

125
00:05:24.075 --> 00:05:25.158
You're safe now.

126
00:05:25.200 --> 00:05:26.200
I got 'em!

127
00:05:29.075 --> 00:05:30.075
They're in the clear.

128
00:05:31.491 --> 00:05:33.741
- You are on President duty.
- On it.

129
00:05:35.033 --> 00:05:37.491
Sorry. I wouldn't normally
move so fast.

130
00:05:37.533 --> 00:05:38.634
but there were
so many of you that...

131
00:05:38.658 --> 00:05:40.450
Oh. no.

132
00:05:40.491 --> 00:05:41.676
It starts with one of you.
then it...

133
00:05:45.283 --> 00:05:47.575
Oh! Sorry.

134
00:05:47.616 --> 00:05:48.658
I can't...

135
00:06:00.825 --> 00:06:01.825
Huh?

136
00:06:03.116 --> 00:06:03.991
Now!

137
00:06:04.033 --> 00:06:05.283
While he's distracted!

138
00:06:05.325 --> 00:06:06.491
This floor looks clear.

139
00:06:06.533 --> 00:06:09.700
I'll go up.
you go down.

140
00:06:48.700 --> 00:06:49.700
I've got you.

141
00:06:49.741 --> 00:06:50.741
We're gonna be fine.

142
00:06:50.783 --> 00:06:52.200
We'll get out of this.

143
00:07:08.533 --> 00:07:12.908
No. no.
what about you?

144
00:07:31.283 --> 00:07:32.908
Behind you.

145
00:07:37.783 --> 00:07:38.991
You're welcome.

146
00:07:39.033 --> 00:07:40.741
Get those soldiers out of here!

147
00:07:44.741 --> 00:07:45.658
We can take it from here.

148
00:07:45.700 --> 00:07:46.866
Too dangerous for you.

149
00:07:48.366 --> 00:07:49.676
When we crush
the Guardians of the Globe

150
00:07:49.700 --> 00:07:51.200
and kill the president.

151
00:07:51.241 --> 00:07:53.700
no one will be left
to stop us!

152
00:08:07.700 --> 00:08:08.741
Take my hand!

153
00:08:11.116 --> 00:08:12.408
I had him.

154
00:08:16.658 --> 00:08:18.283
Ah. All clear.

155
00:08:18.325 --> 00:08:19.991
The building is clear.

156
00:08:20.033 --> 00:08:20.950
It's just us.

157
00:08:20.991 --> 00:08:22.116
Evacuation complete.

158
00:08:22.158 --> 00:08:23.158
Now we can cut loose

159
00:08:23.200 --> 00:08:25.408
and focus on
taking these brutes down.

160
00:08:39.075 --> 00:08:40.741
Ah!

161
00:08:43.408 --> 00:08:44.408
Ah!

162
00:08:59.075 --> 00:09:00.116
Ah!

163
00:09:04.325 --> 00:09:05.616
Ah!

164
00:09:17.658 --> 00:09:19.283
Mom? What!

165
00:09:19.325 --> 00:09:20.325
I'll be out in a minute!

166
00:09:21.075 --> 00:09:21.950
I don't have
a minute.

167
00:09:21.991 --> 00:09:22.783
Mom!

168
00:09:22.825 --> 00:09:23.866
My bathroom's
out of soap.

169
00:09:23.908 --> 00:09:25.283
Get over yourself.

170
00:09:25.325 --> 00:09:27.116
I used to change
your diapers. kid.

171
00:09:27.158 --> 00:09:27.991
There's nothing
going on down there

172
00:09:28.033 --> 00:09:28.866
I haven't seen before.

173
00:09:28.908 --> 00:09:30.783
Just get out!

174
00:09:31.700 --> 00:09:33.366
As you can see.

175
00:09:33.408 --> 00:09:36.533
the scene is absolute chaos
as the Mauler twins...

176
00:09:36.575 --> 00:09:38.450
Looks like
Dad's saving the White House.

177
00:09:38.491 --> 00:09:39.325
Alone?

178
00:09:39.366 --> 00:09:40.616
Guardians are there. too.

179
00:09:40.658 --> 00:09:42.200
Who are they fighting?

180
00:09:42.241 --> 00:09:44.116
Ugh. Mauler Twins.

181
00:09:44.158 --> 00:09:45.551
Looks like we won't be
getting breakfast together

182
00:09:45.575 --> 00:09:46.533
this morning.

183
00:09:46.575 --> 00:09:47.533
Bummer.

184
00:09:47.575 --> 00:09:48.950
It's the White House. Mom.

185
00:09:48.991 --> 00:09:50.200
Kind of important.

186
00:09:50.241 --> 00:09:54.033
Oh. they rebuild that thing
twice a year at this point.

187
00:09:54.075 --> 00:09:55.116
If it's not Doc Seismic.

188
00:09:55.158 --> 00:09:56.908
it's the Lizard League.
or someone else.

189
00:09:56.950 --> 00:09:58.510
I doubt the President
still lives there.

190
00:10:00.783 --> 00:10:01.700
I'm not too late!

191
00:10:01.741 --> 00:10:02.950
I'm gonna shower.

192
00:10:02.991 --> 00:10:04.366
Not so fast.

193
00:10:04.408 --> 00:10:05.533
Come here first.

194
00:10:08.700 --> 00:10:10.700
Don't make me
get the spray bottle.

195
00:10:12.075 --> 00:10:15.325
Now. let's get you
out of that costume.

196
00:10:15.366 --> 00:10:16.783
Boundaries. people!

197
00:10:18.158 --> 00:10:19.700
Bathroom doors
are closed for a reason.

198
00:10:19.741 --> 00:10:21.467
and parents should never.
ever talk about sex

199
00:10:21.491 --> 00:10:23.200
in front of their kids!

200
00:10:23.241 --> 00:10:26.658
You should be overjoyed
to see your parents

201
00:10:26.700 --> 00:10:29.366
passionately expressing
their love for each other.

202
00:10:29.408 --> 00:10:30.783
Now stop griping.

203
00:10:30.825 --> 00:10:31.950
Get ready for school.

204
00:10:31.991 --> 00:10:34.616
Couldn't you at least wait
until I leave the house...

205
00:10:34.658 --> 00:10:35.991
for college!

206
00:10:37.200 --> 00:10:38.741
What were you thinking?

207
00:10:38.783 --> 00:10:39.658
Paris?

208
00:10:39.700 --> 00:10:40.801
Actually.
I was kind of pulling

209
00:10:40.825 --> 00:10:42.158
for that little cafe
in Berlin.

210
00:10:42.200 --> 00:10:44.450
I've been jonesing
for those sausages.

211
00:10:45.366 --> 00:10:46.967
Aw. man. you guys
are going to Best Wurst?

212
00:10:46.991 --> 00:10:48.533
I love that place!

213
00:10:48.575 --> 00:10:49.741
You've got school.

214
00:10:49.783 --> 00:10:51.783
When your powers kick in.
you can go on your own.

215
00:10:51.825 --> 00:10:54.366
Salt on the wound. Dad.

216
00:10:54.408 --> 00:10:57.075
They've gotta be due
any day now. son.

217
00:10:57.116 --> 00:10:59.116
Even the latest bloomers
on Viltrum

218
00:10:59.158 --> 00:11:00.116
would get their powers

219
00:11:00.158 --> 00:11:02.658
before what would be
their 18th birthday.

220
00:11:02.700 --> 00:11:03.741
You'll see.

221
00:11:03.783 --> 00:11:05.063
Don't get his hopes up.

222
00:11:09.116 --> 00:11:10.158
Bye!

223
00:11:10.200 --> 00:11:11.658
Have fun!

224
00:11:11.700 --> 00:11:12.866
I'll just be walking.

225
00:11:12.908 --> 00:11:13.908
on the ground.

226
00:11:13.950 --> 00:11:14.825
with my feet.

227
00:11:33.658 --> 00:11:35.741
Morning.

228
00:11:37.533 --> 00:11:39.158
Uh. just. uh...

229
00:11:39.200 --> 00:11:42.366
just trying to break in
these new shoes.

230
00:11:42.408 --> 00:11:45.283
Ugh!

231
00:11:49.783 --> 00:11:51.950
Mauler Twins
attack the White House?

232
00:11:51.991 --> 00:11:52.991
Nuts. right?

233
00:11:53.033 --> 00:11:54.033
I saw.

234
00:11:54.075 --> 00:11:55.592
I can't believe
the Guardians of the Globe

235
00:11:55.616 --> 00:11:58.366
let them get that close
to killing the President.

236
00:11:58.408 --> 00:11:59.926
They didn't even get
into the building.

237
00:11:59.950 --> 00:12:01.575
and Omni-Man was there. too.

238
00:12:01.616 --> 00:12:04.116
You're such
an Omni-Maniac.

239
00:12:04.158 --> 00:12:05.700
Way to root
for the underdog.

240
00:12:05.741 --> 00:12:07.950
Big fan of the Yankees.
are you?

241
00:12:07.991 --> 00:12:10.033
Sure. he's hot and all.

242
00:12:10.075 --> 00:12:11.533
and that mustache...

243
00:12:12.991 --> 00:12:13.825
Sorry!

244
00:12:13.866 --> 00:12:15.575
Okay. straight stuff.

245
00:12:15.616 --> 00:12:17.075
You up for some
Clash Crash tonight?

246
00:12:17.116 --> 00:12:18.950
I'm hoping for a Level 43
chest armor.

247
00:12:20.908 --> 00:12:22.575
Don't bring up
that stupid job. man.

248
00:12:22.616 --> 00:12:23.783
Don't be that person.

249
00:12:23.825 --> 00:12:25.426
When's the last time
you bought a comic book?

250
00:12:25.450 --> 00:12:26.866
Those things are expensive.

251
00:12:26.908 --> 00:12:29.616
and they're doing Seance Dog
twice a month all summer.

252
00:12:29.658 --> 00:12:31.533
You're into
the stupidest stuff.

253
00:12:31.575 --> 00:12:33.950
Knock it off. Todd!

254
00:12:33.991 --> 00:12:35.366
Come on...

255
00:12:35.408 --> 00:12:36.575
Quit playing games.

256
00:12:36.616 --> 00:12:37.866
I know you're crazy about me.

257
00:12:37.908 --> 00:12:39.450
Marcy told me.

258
00:12:39.491 --> 00:12:42.450
Well. you are
big and strong. aren't you?

259
00:12:42.491 --> 00:12:43.450
You know it.

260
00:12:43.491 --> 00:12:45.366
And you think
that makes it okay

261
00:12:45.408 --> 00:12:46.825
for you to harass me?

262
00:12:46.866 --> 00:12:48.700
Hey. don't walk away from me.

263
00:12:48.741 --> 00:12:50.450
What. are you
a lesbian or something?

264
00:12:50.491 --> 00:12:53.033
Oh. my god. I wish!

265
00:12:53.075 --> 00:12:54.533
Would you
leave me alone then?

266
00:12:54.575 --> 00:12:55.658
Let go of me.

267
00:12:55.700 --> 00:12:57.450
so I can go find
a girl to kiss!

268
00:12:57.491 --> 00:12:58.491
Don't.

269
00:12:58.533 --> 00:12:59.866
Guy's twice your size.

270
00:12:59.908 --> 00:13:01.217
Maybe you can just
sit back and watch this?

271
00:13:01.241 --> 00:13:02.200
I can't.

272
00:13:02.241 --> 00:13:04.241
I can because
I'm not Omni-Man.

273
00:13:04.283 --> 00:13:05.658
and neither are you.

274
00:13:05.700 --> 00:13:07.158
Let's see.

275
00:13:08.366 --> 00:13:09.658
I think Amber's
been pretty clear

276
00:13:09.700 --> 00:13:12.908
about how she feels. Todd.

277
00:13:12.950 --> 00:13:13.908
Are you serious. Grayson?

278
00:13:13.950 --> 00:13:14.950
Look...

279
00:13:20.991 --> 00:13:22.533
Leave him alone!

280
00:13:24.741 --> 00:13:26.116
What are you lookin' at?

281
00:13:30.075 --> 00:13:31.325
Thank you.

282
00:13:31.366 --> 00:13:32.366
Yup.

283
00:14:14.158 --> 00:14:15.616
Close one.

284
00:14:19.450 --> 00:14:20.658
Huh.

285
00:14:21.991 --> 00:14:24.491
It's about time.

286
00:14:28.741 --> 00:14:31.283
And a big welcome home
to my favorite son.

287
00:14:31.325 --> 00:14:32.491
I made some chicken.

288
00:14:32.533 --> 00:14:35.575
but I also heated up
some authentic German bratwurst

289
00:14:35.616 --> 00:14:36.658
flown in special today.

290
00:14:36.700 --> 00:14:37.658
just for you.

291
00:14:37.700 --> 00:14:41.950
I... had
a pretty interesting day.

292
00:14:44.283 --> 00:14:45.450
Sorry I'm late.

293
00:14:45.491 --> 00:14:48.033
Honest to god. a dragon
was attacking Hong Kong.

294
00:14:48.075 --> 00:14:48.908
I stopped it.

295
00:14:48.950 --> 00:14:50.366
Ooh. a dragon.
Nice.

296
00:14:50.408 --> 00:14:51.783
Mark was getting ready
to tell us

297
00:14:51.825 --> 00:14:53.283
how interesting
his day was.

298
00:14:53.325 --> 00:14:56.866
Guess who's finally
getting his powers?

299
00:14:58.325 --> 00:14:59.616
Are you sure?

300
00:14:59.658 --> 00:15:01.241
Pretty sure.

301
00:15:01.283 --> 00:15:03.783
Threw a trash bag into space
at work.

302
00:15:06.158 --> 00:15:08.616
Oh. that's great. Son.

303
00:15:08.658 --> 00:15:09.866
just great!

304
00:15:09.908 --> 00:15:10.991
