I can't do this!

548
00:26:57.033 --> 00:26:58.616
Hit me. and let me
prove you wrong!

549
00:26:58.658 --> 00:26:59.950
Please. Dad!

550
00:26:59.991 --> 00:27:01.325
Please just hit me.

551
00:27:01.366 --> 00:27:02.908
Oh. Son...

552
00:27:02.950 --> 00:27:05.533
I'm strong enough.
and I can do this!

553
00:27:05.575 --> 00:27:07.991
It's all I ever wanted
for as long as I can remember.

554
00:27:08.033 --> 00:27:11.908
I wanna do what you do.

555
00:27:11.950 --> 00:27:14.575
I wanna be just like you.

556
00:27:17.741 --> 00:27:20.075
You will be. Son.

557
00:27:20.116 --> 00:27:21.616
You will.

558
00:27:24.533 --> 00:27:27.200
Let me make this up to you.

559
00:27:31.283 --> 00:27:32.783
Follow me.

560
00:27:39.450 --> 00:27:40.467
You're taking me shopping?

561
00:27:40.491 --> 00:27:43.200
I am.

562
00:27:52.241 --> 00:27:53.450
Were you seen?

563
00:27:53.491 --> 00:27:55.158
Who are you talking to?

564
00:27:55.200 --> 00:27:56.741
Sorry. sorry.

565
00:27:56.783 --> 00:27:57.991
Just need to ask.

566
00:27:58.033 --> 00:27:58.950
Whoa...

567
00:27:58.991 --> 00:28:01.283
Prom dresses by day.

568
00:28:01.325 --> 00:28:04.616
indestructible super suits
by night.

569
00:28:04.658 --> 00:28:06.366
I'm Art Rosenbaum. kid.

570
00:28:06.408 --> 00:28:07.991
Pleasure to finally meet you.

571
00:28:08.033 --> 00:28:09.866
I've heard so much
about you.

572
00:28:09.908 --> 00:28:11.908
You. too.

573
00:28:11.950 --> 00:28:12.991
Heh.

574
00:28:13.033 --> 00:28:14.783
Your dad's never
mentioned me. has he?

575
00:28:14.825 --> 00:28:16.116
Well. I...

576
00:28:16.158 --> 00:28:17.158
He's a teenager. Art.

577
00:28:17.200 --> 00:28:18.325
He barely remembers anything

578
00:28:18.366 --> 00:28:20.116
he doesn't see in the mirror
every morning.

579
00:28:21.033 --> 00:28:22.575
Wait. super suits?

580
00:28:22.616 --> 00:28:24.116
Am I getting
a costume?

581
00:28:24.158 --> 00:28:25.700
Do you make
Dad's costumes?

582
00:28:25.741 --> 00:28:27.200
He's a quick one.
this kid.

583
00:28:27.241 --> 00:28:28.426
I can't have you
running around in your pajamas

584
00:28:28.450 --> 00:28:29.283
all the time.

585
00:28:29.325 --> 00:28:30.658
Oh. man!

586
00:28:30.700 --> 00:28:31.825
Awesome!

587
00:28:31.866 --> 00:28:33.301
Wait. do you already
have one made for me?

588
00:28:33.325 --> 00:28:34.325
Is it a surprise?

589
00:28:34.366 --> 00:28:36.283
Usually. we start
with a conversation.

590
00:28:36.325 --> 00:28:38.283
and I make something custom.

591
00:28:38.325 --> 00:28:40.533
but I do have one
that might work.

592
00:28:43.408 --> 00:28:45.450
What do you think?

593
00:28:45.491 --> 00:28:46.533
Well...

594
00:28:46.575 --> 00:28:48.241
I don't know about
the orange and yellow.

595
00:28:48.283 --> 00:28:49.158
It's pretty loud.

596
00:28:49.200 --> 00:28:50.033
Dad?

597
00:28:50.075 --> 00:28:52.200
Not your best work. Art.

598
00:28:52.241 --> 00:28:53.950
Can't blame a guy

599
00:28:53.991 --> 00:28:56.450
for trying to move
unsold merchandise.

600
00:28:57.450 --> 00:28:58.741
I like the goggles.

601
00:28:58.783 --> 00:29:01.158
They'd keep the wind
out of my eyes when I fly.

602
00:29:01.200 --> 00:29:04.366
but I was really. like.
hoping for something more. uh...

603
00:29:04.408 --> 00:29:05.366
I don't know...

604
00:29:05.408 --> 00:29:06.366
iconic?

605
00:29:06.408 --> 00:29:07.991
Of course you were.

606
00:29:08.033 --> 00:29:09.866
That's what everyone wants.

607
00:29:09.908 --> 00:29:10.783
Iconic.

608
00:29:10.825 --> 00:29:11.866
A symbol.

609
00:29:11.908 --> 00:29:13.491
Something kids
will draw

610
00:29:13.533 --> 00:29:15.033
in the margins
of their notebooks

611
00:29:15.075 --> 00:29:18.116
while they daydream about
being as cool as you.

612
00:29:18.158 --> 00:29:19.783
It's also tough as hell
to pull off.

613
00:29:19.825 --> 00:29:21.116
but listen.

614
00:29:21.158 --> 00:29:23.075
your dad being who he is.

615
00:29:23.116 --> 00:29:25.075
I'm willing to put
a lot of elbow grease

616
00:29:25.116 --> 00:29:26.158
into this one...

617
00:29:26.200 --> 00:29:28.533
but I'm gonna need
a little help from you.

618
00:29:28.575 --> 00:29:30.283
Have you decided on a name yet?

619
00:29:30.325 --> 00:29:32.283
I haven't really
thought about it.

620
00:29:32.325 --> 00:29:34.033
Well. having a name helps.

621
00:29:34.075 --> 00:29:36.075
Darkwing has dark wings.

622
00:29:36.116 --> 00:29:38.783
the Red Rush is a red rush
when he runs by you.

623
00:29:38.825 --> 00:29:39.866
You get it?

624
00:29:39.908 --> 00:29:41.158
You give me
something to go on.

625
00:29:41.200 --> 00:29:42.741
I'll strive for iconic.

626
00:29:42.783 --> 00:29:44.200
Think about it
and get back to me.

627
00:29:50.616 --> 00:29:52.033
Mark?

628
00:29:58.158 --> 00:29:59.616
Mark?

629
00:30:07.408 --> 00:30:08.408
Mark?

630
00:30:22.158 --> 00:30:23.533
What the hell was that?

631
00:30:24.616 --> 00:30:25.741
Uh...

632
00:30:25.783 --> 00:30:27.033
practicing my landings?

633
00:30:27.075 --> 00:30:29.700
Yeah. I see that now.

634
00:30:29.741 --> 00:30:30.658
Yeah. uh...

635
00:30:30.700 --> 00:30:32.200
sorry about the yard.

636
00:30:32.241 --> 00:30:33.450
What are you doing?

637
00:30:33.491 --> 00:30:35.116
I need practice. Mom.

638
00:30:35.158 --> 00:30:38.200
I can't land well.
I can't fly all that fast.

639
00:30:38.241 --> 00:30:39.033
I need to be better.

640
00:30:39.075 --> 00:30:41.283
Mark. you need to sleep.

641
00:30:41.325 --> 00:30:42.783
I need to practice.

642
00:30:42.825 --> 00:30:44.051
Honey it's the middle
of the night.

643
00:30:44.075 --> 00:30:46.158
I have work tomorrow.
you have school.

644
00:30:46.200 --> 00:30:47.700
Get inside right now.

645
00:30:48.700 --> 00:30:49.700
Make me.

646
00:30:51.200 --> 00:30:52.783
Does that make you feel strong?

647
00:30:52.825 --> 00:30:55.241
To know I can't physically
make you do something?

648
00:30:55.283 --> 00:30:56.700
Is that what you need?

649
00:30:58.241 --> 00:31:00.658
This is important.

650
00:31:03.366 --> 00:31:04.950
Remember when
you were little.

651
00:31:04.991 --> 00:31:06.450
and we'd talk
almost every night

652
00:31:06.491 --> 00:31:07.950
before you went to bed?

653
00:31:07.991 --> 00:31:09.116
You'd tell me

654
00:31:09.158 --> 00:31:11.575
about whatever jerk
made fun of your hair.

655
00:31:11.616 --> 00:31:13.783
and I'd tell you about
all the girl drama

656
00:31:13.825 --> 00:31:14.866
I lived through

657
00:31:14.908 --> 00:31:15.908
so you'd feel better?

658
00:31:16.991 --> 00:31:18.075
I can't talk to you

659
00:31:18.116 --> 00:31:19.741
while we soar
through the clouds.

660
00:31:19.783 --> 00:31:22.908
but... but I'm still here.

661
00:31:25.200 --> 00:31:26.700
It used to be
you and me.

662
00:31:26.741 --> 00:31:28.116
and this crazy
world-saving.

663
00:31:28.158 --> 00:31:30.575
super-powered
father of yours.

664
00:31:30.616 --> 00:31:32.658
Now it's you and him.

665
00:31:32.700 --> 00:31:34.991
and your boring. old.
normal mom.

666
00:31:35.033 --> 00:31:35.991
Mom...

667
00:31:36.033 --> 00:31:36.991
It's okay. sweetheart.

668
00:31:37.033 --> 00:31:38.283
I get it.

669
00:31:38.325 --> 00:31:41.616
You have to move away
from the normal life with me.

670
00:31:41.658 --> 00:31:43.616
and get used to being...

671
00:31:43.658 --> 00:31:44.783
something more.

672
00:31:44.825 --> 00:31:45.991
like your dad.

673
00:31:46.033 --> 00:31:48.283
Yeah. but see.
that's what I'm worried about.

674
00:31:48.325 --> 00:31:50.408
I'm nothing like Dad.

675
00:31:50.450 --> 00:31:52.116
I'm more like you.

676
00:31:52.158 --> 00:31:53.533
I'm nothing special.

677
00:31:53.575 --> 00:31:55.616
Oh...

678
00:31:55.658 --> 00:31:58.575
Like a knife to the heart
with this one.

679
00:31:58.616 --> 00:32:00.158
Ah... crap.

680
00:32:00.200 --> 00:32:01.491
You know what I mean.

681
00:32:01.533 --> 00:32:03.158
After everything he's done.

682
00:32:03.200 --> 00:32:06.491
how could I possibly
live up to all that?

683
00:32:06.533 --> 00:32:07.991
Who says you have to?

684
00:32:08.033 --> 00:32:11.200
You don't have to be
the greatest Omni-Man ever.

685
00:32:11.241 --> 00:32:14.741
You just have to be
the greatest you.

686
00:32:14.783 --> 00:32:17.741
And what if the greatest me
isn't enough?

687
00:32:17.783 --> 00:32:19.408
Mark. you stupid boy.

688
00:32:19.450 --> 00:32:21.741
How could the greatest you
not be enough?

689
00:32:22.741 --> 00:32:23.950
Thank you.

690
00:32:23.991 --> 00:32:25.366
I love my boring.

691
00:32:25.408 --> 00:32:27.700
powerless. everyday.
run-of-the-mill Mom.

692
00:32:27.741 --> 00:32:31.200
And I love my asshole son.

693
00:32:43.491 --> 00:32:45.658
You seem tired.

694
00:32:45.700 --> 00:32:47.741
I'm fine.

695
00:32:47.783 --> 00:32:50.700
Just got...
a lot on my mind. I guess.

696
00:32:52.783 --> 00:32:54.033
Oh. yeah?

697
00:32:54.075 --> 00:32:55.866
So. what is it?

698
00:32:55.908 --> 00:32:57.575
You're just gonna keep prying

699
00:32:57.616 --> 00:33:00.866
if I'm evasive at all.
so. um...

700
00:33:00.908 --> 00:33:02.616
I'm scared. Dad.

701
00:33:03.450 --> 00:33:06.033
What if I can't do this?

702
00:33:08.991 --> 00:33:10.283
You hear it?

703
00:33:10.325 --> 00:33:11.116
I do.

704
00:33:11.158 --> 00:33:12.533
Get ready.

705
00:33:14.283 --> 00:33:15.700
Were you nervous?

706
00:33:15.741 --> 00:33:16.950
A little.

707
00:33:17.908 --> 00:33:19.116
But you caught it?

708
00:33:19.158 --> 00:33:20.908
I did.

709
00:33:20.950 --> 00:33:22.700
Being a superhero
is no different.

710
00:33:22.741 --> 00:33:24.866
This is the beginning
of a long journey

711
00:33:24.908 --> 00:33:26.158
for you and me.

712
00:33:26.200 --> 00:33:27.991
Along the way.

713
00:33:28.033 --> 00:33:29.092
you're gonna need
to do things

714
00:33:29.116 --> 00:33:30.950
you don't want to do.

715
00:33:30.991 --> 00:33:32.908
or might not think
you can do.

716
00:33:32.950 --> 00:33:35.241
It's okay to be scared.

717
00:33:35.283 --> 00:33:37.450
It's natural
to doubt yourself.

718
00:33:37.491 --> 00:33:38.991
but if you can
push through that.

719
00:33:39.033 --> 00:33:40.908
and do what needs to be done.

720
00:33:40.950 --> 00:33:43.116
you'll do just fine.

721
00:33:43.158 --> 00:33:45.158
Do you think
you can do that. Mark?

722
00:33:46.116 --> 00:33:47.116
Yeah.

723
00:33:56.116 --> 00:33:57.325
Son...

724
00:33:57.366 --> 00:33:59.658
kids your age
think they're invincible.

725
00:33:59.700 --> 00:34:00.616
and it holds them back.

726
00:34:00.658 --> 00:34:01.825
makes them careless.

727
00:34:01.866 --> 00:34:03.825
The thing is...

728
00:34:03.866 --> 00:34:05.825
you're different.

729
00:34:05.866 --> 00:34:07.700
You actually are...

730
00:34:09.158 --> 00:34:10.491
invincible.

731
00:34:17.866 --> 00:34:19.075
Got it.

732
00:34:19.116 --> 00:34:20.950
Okay. kid.

733
00:34:20.991 --> 00:34:22.325
Let's get to work.

734
00:34:58.116 --> 00:35:00.575
♪ I was born on the wrong side ♪
♪ of the train tracks ♪

735
00:35:00.616 --> 00:35:03.616
♪ I was raised with the strap ♪
♪ across my back ♪

736
00:35:03.658 --> 00:35:07.575
♪ Lay me on my side ♪
♪ or hold me up to the light ♪

737
00:35:07.616 --> 00:35:09.033
♪ Yeah ♪

738
00:35:09.075 --> 00:35:12.283
♪ I was burned by the cold kiss ♪
♪ of a vampire ♪

739
00:35:12.325 --> 00:35:15.283
♪ I was bit by the whisper ♪
♪ of a soft liar ♪

740
00:35:15.325 --> 00:35:18.158
♪ Any good friend of yours ♪
♪ is a good friend of mine ♪

741
00:35:21.616 --> 00:35:24.241
♪ Broken boy ♪

742
00:35:24.283 --> 00:35:27.158
♪ How does it feel? ♪

743
00:35:27.200 --> 00:35:29.616
♪ Broken boy ♪

744
00:35:29.658 --> 00:35:32.283
♪ How does it feel? ♪
♪ How does it feel? ♪

745
00:35:42.825 --> 00:35:45.033
♪ Tell me why I'm forced ♪
♪ to live in this skin ♪

746
00:35:45.075 --> 00:35:48.325
♪ Tell me why I was born ♪
♪ to live in this skin ♪

747
00:35:48.366 --> 00:35:52.366
♪ I'm an alien ♪
♪ Not just an alien ♪

748
00:35:52.408 --> 00:35:53.491
♪ Oh! ♪

749
00:35:56.575 --> 00:35:58.075
Crap.

750
00:36:08.908 --> 00:36:10.533
You guys think
you might have bitten off

751
00:36:10.575 --> 00:36:11.658
more than you can chew?

752
00:36:11.700 --> 00:36:14.616
That building
has a hole in it. look!

753
00:36:19.408 --> 00:36:21.200
Shit!

754
00:36:36.116 --> 00:36:37.116
Whoa...

755
00:36:37.908 --> 00:36:39.200
All clear?

756
00:36:39.241 --> 00:36:40.283
Whoo!

757
00:36:45.741 --> 00:36:47.241
Ow!

758
00:37:03.575 --> 00:37:04.616
Huh?

759
00:37:05.741 --> 00:37:07.116
You might as well give up.

760
00:37:07.158 --> 00:37:08.158
I'm...

761
00:37:15.325 --> 00:37:19.200
I just mean.
he is a fish person.

762
00:37:19.241 --> 00:37:21.491
I think you should maybe
be nicer to him.

763
00:37:21.533 --> 00:37:23.658
It must be hard for him
to make friends.

764
00:37:23.700 --> 00:37:26.241
He's got a whole ocean
of friends.

765
00:37:26.283 --> 00:37:27.700
but you're right. I'll...

766
00:37:28.533 --> 00:37:31.491
Run!

767
00:37:31.533 --> 00:37:33.283
I want to see fear in your eyes!

768
00:37:33.325 --> 00:37:35.366
The same fear...

769
00:37:35.408 --> 00:37:37.033
What is this?

770
00:37:37.075 --> 00:37:38.408
I do my best

771
00:37:38.450 --> 00:37:40.533
to make friends
with the guy.

772
00:37:40.575 --> 00:37:41.700
Josef!

773
00:37:41.741 --> 00:37:42.616
You promised!

774
00:37:42.658 --> 00:37:44.866
Huh? Oh. crap.

775
00:37:44.908 --> 00:37:46.241
How is this going to work

776
00:37:46.283 --> 00:37:49.616
if I can't hold your interest
through one conversation?

777
00:37:49.658 --> 00:37:50.783
Hold my interest?

778
00:37:50.825 --> 00:37:51.991
Olga. please.

779
00:37:52.033 --> 00:37:54.033
You can't see things how I do.

780
00:37:54.075 --> 00:37:55.950
My perception
is just as fast as I am.

781
00:37:55.991 --> 00:37:57.741
The briefest conversation
with anyone

782
00:37:57.783 --> 00:37:59.116
seems like hours to me.

783
00:37:59.158 --> 00:38:00.366
It's agony.

784
00:38:03.408 --> 00:38:07.533
But with you. it's a gift.

785
00:38:07.575 --> 00:38:10.950
Your voice is like music.

786
00:38:10.991 --> 00:38:12.908
You're thoughtful.
compassionate.

787
00:38:12.950 --> 00:38:14.575
beautiful woman.

788
00:38:14.616 --> 00:38:17.825
I hang on every word.

789
00:38:18.741 --> 00:38:19.533
Hmm.

790
00:38:19.575 --> 00:38:21.075
You mean that?

791
00:38:21.116 --> 00:38:21.950
I do.

792
00:38:25.200 --> 00:38:26.408
That's...

793
00:38:26.450 --> 00:38:27.908
Guardians emergency.

794
00:38:27.950 --> 00:38:28.908
I'm so very sorry.

795
00:38:28.950 --> 00:38:30.325
I understand.

796
00:38:30.366 --> 00:38:31.741
Go.

797
00:38:41.700 --> 00:38:44.450
Denver is toast. Immortal!

798
00:38:44.491 --> 00:38:45.908
I'm going out.

799
00:38:45.950 --> 00:38:48.908
and I'm taking
the whole city with me!

800
00:38:48.950 --> 00:38:50.658
I've lined my suit

801
00:38:50.700 --> 00:38:52.116
with plutonium!

802
00:38:54.616 --> 00:38:56.783
When in doubt.
throw them into space.

803
00:38:56.825 --> 00:38:58.908
Huh?

804
00:39:17.075 --> 00:39:19.700
Finally. some action!

805
00:39:26.533 --> 00:39:28.450
Holly. wait up!

806
00:39:28.491 --> 00:39:29.408
Please. Connie.

807
00:39:29.450 --> 00:39:30.991
don't waste
any more of my time.

808
00:39:31.033 --> 00:39:33.033
This is good news.

809
00:39:33.075 --> 00:39:35.741
With our third quarter roll-out
of Haven Storm 4.0.

810
00:39:35.783 --> 00:39:39.325
our market share should rise
by a minimum of 10%.

811
00:39:39.366 --> 00:39:41.866
We have a spectacular year
ahead of us.

812
00:39:41.908 --> 00:39:43.116
The new roll-out
of Haven Storm

813
00:39:43.158 --> 00:39:44.575
was supposed
to be free.

814
00:39:44.616 --> 00:39:46.825
I'm not worried
about the shareholders' year.

815
00:39:46.866 --> 00:39:49.075
I want a spectacular year
for the world.

816
00:39:51.116 --> 00:39:53.825
Don't you do enough
for the world?

817
00:39:53.866 --> 00:39:55.241
None of us do.

818
00:40:05.908 --> 00:40:07.116
Come on!

819
00:40:09.075 --> 00:40:10.783
Come on. you're almost there!

820
00:40:10.825 --> 00:40:12.366
You got this!

821
00:40:13.700 --> 00:40:15.200
You did it!
You did it!

822
00:40:19.783 --> 00:40:21.033
Oh. crap.
Sorry!

823
00:40:22.658 --> 00:40:25.283
Okay. got it.

824
00:40:29.450 --> 00:40:31.825
Are you okay?

825
00:40:31.866 --> 00:40:32.991
I am fine.

826
00:40:33.033 --> 00:40:33.991
We did it.

827
00:40:34.033 --> 00:40:36.533
I'd never expanded myself
to that extent.

828
00:40:36.575 --> 00:40:38.658
That was... intense.

829
00:40:40.575 --> 00:40:42.783
Aw. man. take me with you.

830
00:40:42.825 --> 00:40:44.158
Come on. I can help!

831
00:40:44.200 --> 00:40:45.366
No. Nikki.

832
00:40:45.408 --> 00:40:47.950
You know Guardians' business
is too dangerous

833
00:40:47.991 --> 00:40:50.033
for human children.

834
00:40:50.075 --> 00:40:51.158
Oh. man...

835
00:40:53.158 --> 00:40:54.342
Aw. you're doing
so good. That's it!

836
00:40:54.366 --> 00:40:56.616
Ooh. yes. like that.
Like that!

837
00:40:56.658 --> 00:40:57.533
Keep going.

838
00:40:57.575 --> 00:40:58.825
Aw. yes. yes. yes.

839
00:40:58.866 --> 00:40:59.866
hold that. hold that.

840
00:41:01.033 --> 00:41:02.825
What is that beeping?

841
00:41:05.491 --> 00:41:06.450
Uh...

842
00:41:06.491 --> 00:41:07.450
That's a wrap.

843
00:41:07.491 --> 00:41:08.491
Uh. great work. everyone!

844
00:41:21.616 --> 00:41:23.575
